The paper discusses the development of a measure for bounding the performance of AND/OR search algorithms for solving queries over graphical models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper draws a connection to hypertree decompositions, which are commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses practical problem instances, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of search algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
